vyges-geom is a std-only Rust crate providing axis-aligned rectangle geometry
primitives and a uniform-grid spatial index (RegionIndex) for region / overlap /
spacing-halo queries. It is the geometry substrate the Vyges layout-side tools
(vyges-layout, and through it LVS device extraction, DRC, and the chip viewer)
share; it is a linked library, not a user-facing tool.

This is a clean-room implementation; no third-party EDA database is included.
